The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 05 January is 21,578 (2,497.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 31 December, there were 5,126 new confirmed cases (593.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 24 December, there were 2,878 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 78% (2,248 extra cases).
